And if you can't afford to give someone something and you don't wanna make eye contact, whatever. I'm not here to please. How you interact with people. But these are people I knew could give. These are people I would see go in and pull out a lot of money, and I'll be like, hey, can you buy me something? They be like, I don't have money. And it's like, okay, whatever. And they would feed me and they wouldn't feed me crap either. It wasn't yesterday's bread or a peanut butter and jelly sandwich. It was a heaping to go container of the best foods that they like. But I remember one time this guy said, let me get you some food, you look hungry. And I was like, I'm so hungry. And he brought me food and he brought me an entire picture of water to sit and drink. القيمة السوقية للرجل في المجتمع تحددها ثلاث عوامل و هي: المال، المنصب، الشهرة.  أما القيمة السوقية للأنثى فتأتي من ثلاث خصائص و هي: صغر السن، الجمال، العفة. فالرجل يكون مطلوبا إذا كان لديه مستقبل، بينما الأنثى تكون مرغوبة إذا لم يكن لديها ماض. و الرجل كلما كان محاطا بالنساء أكثر زاد عليه الطلب و تنافست النسوة فيما بينهن للظفر بقلبه لأنه سيد الرجال، أما المرأة فعلى العكس تماما إذ كلما كانت بعيدة عن الرجال كلما كلما كانت مرغوبة لكونها شريفة عفيفة. فالرجل حينما يكون وحيدا تزهد فيه النساء، و ما أن يرتبط حتى تأتيه أفضل العروض من أقوى الأندية. و معظم النساء يفتخرن دوما بالمستوى المادي و المكانة الاجتماعية  لأزواجهن، لكن نادرا ما تجد امرأة تفتخر بأخلاق زوجها و تدينه و علمه. و الرجال الضعفاء يصنعون نسويات مسترجلات، بينما الرجال الأقوياء يخلقون نساءا أنثويات، فالمرأة تخضع للرجل ذي الشخصية الكاريزمية القيادية، و تتمرد على الرجل المنبطح المتساهل المستهتر الذي يعاني من خور في الشخصية و خلل في تقدير الذات و الثقة في النفس. ألم تر أنه حينما يخون الفقير زوجته فإنها تقول لصديقتها: لقد خانني الوغد. أما حينما يخون الثري زوجته فإنها تقول: الحقيرة تريد سرقة زوجي.  فالمرأة تنجذب للرجل المتصف بالثالوث المظلم في علم النفس و هو: الميكيافيلية، النرجسية، السكوباتية، و هذه الصفات لا يستطيع الذكر العادي البسيط التظاهر بها لأن المرأة لديها حاسة سادسة قوية تمكنها من التمييز بسهولة بين الرجل القوي و الرجل الضعيف. و جدير بالذكرأن الأنثى تولد جاهزة في القمة و كلما تقدم بها السن فقدت جمالها و voice_to_text: My name is Sarah Wilkinson, and I'm about to, uh, sail to Gaza on board the Freedom Flotilla. We have three ships, two passenger ships, one cargo ship carrying 5,500 tons of humanitarian aid, including food and medical supplies. But we also have eight ambulances and one fire engine. voice_to_text: There's been an update on the California doctor who drove his Tesla off of a 250 foot cliff with his 41 year old wife, seven year old girl and four year old boy inside the vehicle. Dalmaish Patel was charged with three counts of attempted murder after he drove his car off of Devil's Slide and landed on the shore of the Pacific Ocean. But miraculously his wife and children all survived. The father pled not guilty claiming that the Tesla was experiencing tire issues at the time. But his own wife says that's a lie. He was just depressed. He's a doctor. He was going to drive off that cliff and he purposefully did. Now his defense is arguing that he suffered from major depressive disorder and he experienced a psychotic break during the incident. Two doctors testified that he was experiencing hallucinations, hearing footsteps and believe that his children were as teeth. And they just had a hearing on Wednesday saying Patel is now seeking a mental health diversion in the case. If accepted, it means he would be put on a two year treatment plan instead of receiving any jail time. And if he doesn't commit any crimes during that time, all charges against him would be dropped. Prosecutors are completely opposed to this saying that he suffered from schizoaffective disorder, not major depressive disorder with a psychotic feature, therefore the treatment wouldn't work. I'll keep you guys updated as the trial continues, do you guys think He was having a mental health crisis at the time. Or do you think he did it on purpose? Let me know in the comments.

voice_to_text: This cat was a mayor of a town and even survived an assassination attempt. This is Stubbs, a cat, and it said that in 1997, residents of a small town in Alaska were so fed up with the candidates running for election that they decided to ride in votes for Stubbs. The local friendly cat later became so popular he ran for the US Senate. Every afternoon, Stubbs went to a nearby restaurant and drink water mixed with catnip out of a wine glass, probably because all of the stress he had from his multiple assassination attempts. Stubbs was one shot by teenagers and recovered, but almost lost his life after being mauled by his opposition, a local dog. Word got out about that. Thousands of people from all around the world started donating money to pay for Stubbs Recovery. He also once fell in a restaurant's deep fryer, but luckily it was switched off and cool at the time. He also accidentally got himself into a garbage truck and hitched a long ride outside the town. Stubbs didn't get much done as mayor, but he became so popular it's estimated he brought in about 30 to 40 tours to the town each day. Stubbs passed away in 2017 and the town appointed the new cat as the next mayor, Denali.

voice_to_text: Whatever happened to Disney Channel's version of Bruce Lee, Leo Howard? In 2005, Leo Howard made his first ever TV sitcom guest appearance as he played Little Karate Kid in an episode of monk. But it wasn't until 2009 when Leo Howard's acting career took off as he acted in the box office smash hit GI Joe rise of the Cobra. Right after Leo's appearance in GI Joe, Disney came knocking on his door, casting him in anything and everything on their network. After a year of Leo Howard being soft launched onto Disney Channel, they finally decided to give him his own show as the lead playing Jack Brewer in Kickin it. By all accounts, Kickin it is one of the most successful shows to ever air on Disney, lasting four seasons. And in that four season of Kickin it, Leo Howard became the youngest person to ever direct an episode of television at just the age of sixteen. As for Leo Howard's acting career post Disney Channel, it did not slow down one bit as he acted in projects such as freakish, The Vampire Diaries, spin off series legacies and why women kill. voice_to_text: Thanks to a deathbed confession, a nearly 24 year old cold case was closed this week when the bodies of a missing girl and her mother were found. Ten year old Natasha Alex Carter and her mother Susan disappeared from their home in Beckley, West Virginia in August 2000. But at first police initially reported that Alex may have been abducted by her mother. In a press release from December 2021 about the case, the FBI Pittsburgh said quote at the time of their disappearance, Susan Carter and Alex's father were having a custody dispute and Alex moved in with her mother and mother's new husband, which it's not confirmed that it was actually her mother's new husband, but they moved in and then not long after that, Susan and Alex disappeared. But while it was initially suspected as a parental abduction by Susan after the two remained missing, an investigation into other possibilities ensued, but unfortunately the case went cold. In 2021, the FBI reopened the cold case and started looking into the man Susan and Alex were living with, Larry Webb, which is of his home. Were done in 2022 and 2023 and they found a bullet embedded in the wall of what was Alex's bedroom. Bullet was tested for DNA and it confirmed that blood on it belonged to Alex. In October 2023, Larry Webb was indicted on first degree murder charges for Alex's death, despite Alex and Susan's bodies never being found due to his deteriorating health. Though Webb was Not arrested until April 12th, 2024, but since then he was being held without bond. On Monday he had a medical episode, after which, in a quote, come to Jesus moment on his deathbed, he confessed to authorities what he had done. Upclaimed that on August 8th, 2000, he had gotten into an argument with Susan over money. He said he was missing some cash and believed that she had taken it and spent it. The argument escalated and he shot her, and then he ended up shooting Alex so there would be no witnesses. Webb then wrapped their bodies in bed linens and placed them in the basement that night. Over the next two nights, he dug a shallow grave in the woods on his property, eventually burying them in his clothes and then walking free for the next 20 years. On April 22nd, 2024, Larry Webb died at Mount Olive Correctional Complex, and six hours later, Susan and Alex's remains were found at his property in Beckley. Fortunately, now that Webb is dead, he cannot be charged in connection to their deaths. At least now they have been found and can be properly laid to rest. Alex's father, Rick Lafferty, said after the discovery, quote, it's kind of a sad day, but also a happy day because I can bring my baby home. Rest in peace, Alex and Susan.
